Kelisha will make history as the first neurodivergent actress to play a neurodivergent character at @youngbrooklynkingproductions

Good evening all! Today is the first day of Autism Awareness month and just want to celebrate this beautiful daughter of mine! The road to discovery for Jahara was not easy but she will definitely help encourage you and herself to not STOP!

Jahara was two years old when I realized something developmentally was not right. She literally stopped talking! Only mumbles and pointing. I was totally baffled and confused as to what happened? What did I do wrong? What did I not do?

As a mother the first thing you do is bare the entire burden on yourself and I blame yourself for affecting her entire life and why did GOD place this upon me?! But why not me?!

Jahara is constantly surprising me and filling me with pride the more she progresses! Now a 9th grader, A Honor Roll student, doing work at her grade level independently and now she does not hold her tongue!ü§£

I love being her mom! The things I've learned about the spectrum and how I've been able to share that knowledge with others and ease some of their worry is so fulfilling. I never knew I'd be here but here WE are! I love you past the moon!
 Go and learn more about the spectrum and help support others in your life that are special needs and their care givers; trust me they need it and appreciate it!
#autismmom #autism365 #blackautisticgirl
